{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"1. **`internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`** — Added `StatusWriter` field and `executeStreaming()` method. When StatusWriter is set, pipes stdout/stderr and streams each line through `StatusWriter.Log()` in real-time instead of buffering with `CombinedOutput()`.","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.051524823Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.051545773Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"2. **`internal/agent/runner.go`** — Wires the `StatusWriter` into the generic adapter so script steps stream output through the same status protocol path that agent/prompt steps use.","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.05154951Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.051572142Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"3. **`internal/protocol/status.go`** — Added flush support: after each JSON status message is encoded, calls `Flush()` on the underlying writer if it implements the `flusher` interface, ensuring immediate delivery.","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.051578875Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.05158658Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"4. **`internal/logstream/logstream.go`** — Added `file.Sync()` after each log write to ensure the unified `full.log` is flushed to disk immediately.","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.051589966Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:32:30.05159737Z"}
